  "prompt": "Knock knee cause any problem in Delhi police si selection?",
  "response": "Knock knees (genu valgum) might potentially affect your selection in the Delhi Police SI (Sub-Inspector) recruitment process, depending on the severity and any associated functional limitations. Here are some key points to consider:\n\n1. **Medical Standards**: Delhi Police recruitment has specific medical standards, including physical fitness and health criteria. Knock knees could be evaluated during the medical examination.\n\n2. **Severity**: Mild knock knees may not be an issue if they do not impair your mobility or physical performance. However, severe cases that affect your ability to perform physical tasks (e.g., running, marching, or other strenuous activities) could disqualify you.\n\n3. **Physical Efficiency Test (PET)**: The selection process includes physical tests such as running, long jump, and high jump. If knock knees limit your ability to perform these tasks effectively, it could impact your selection.\n\n4. **Discretion of Medical Board**: The final decision lies with the medical board conducting the examination. They will assess whether your condition hinders your ability to perform the duties of a Sub-Inspector.\n\n5. **Treatment and Correction**: If your knock knees are mild or correctable, addressing the condition through physiotherapy, exercise, or medical treatment might improve your chances of clearing the medical examination.\n\nIf you\u2019re concerned, it\u2019s a good idea to consult a medical professional to evaluate your condition and its impact on your physical abilities. Additionally, refer to the official **Delhi Police recruitment notification** for detailed medical standards and eligibility criteria.",
